{"parse":{"title":"Cooling board","pageid":2379843,"revid":783560704,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>cooling board</b> was a perforated wooden platform on which a dead body would be temporarily stored and prepared for a funeral. Ice was placed beneath it to keep the body chilled, slowing the decomposition process. Holes in the cooling board, which could be made of cane latticework rather than a solid wooden plank, allowed blood and other fluids to drain from the body. It could also be used to display the body for a viewing if the casket was not delivered in time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sweeney_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sweeney-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Metal embalming tables replaced cooling boards as modern refrigeration became available.\n</p><p>The cooling board is referred to in a number of <a href=\"/wiki/Blues\" title=\"Blues\">blues</a> songs, such as \"Cooling Board Blues\" by <a href=\"/wiki/Blind_Willie_McTell\" title=\"Blind Willie McTell\">Blind Willie McTell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sweeney_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sweeney-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Son_House\" title=\"Son House\">Son House</a> also makes a reference to a cooling board in his \"<a href=\"/wiki/Death_Letter\" title=\"Death Letter\">Death Letter</a>\".\n</p>\n<dl><dd><i>So, I grabbed up my suitcase, and took off down the road.</i></dd>\n<dd><i>When I got there she was layin on a coolin' board.</i></dd></dl>\n<p>A cooling board is also found in a song, \"Thank You, Master (For My Soul)\",  by the late <a href=\"/wiki/Donnie_Hathaway\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Donnie Hathaway\">Donnie Hathaway</a>:<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><i> 'cause the walls of my room was not the walls of my grave</i></dd>\n<dd><i>my bed was not my cooling board (y'all don't know what i'm talkin' 'bout)</i></dd></dl>\n<p>Benjamin B. French witnessed Abraham Lincoln's remains, after transfer from the Peterson House to the White House, being \"taken from the box in which they were enclosed, all limp and warm, and laid upon the floor, and then stretched upon the cooling board.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cooling_board&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Sweeney-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Sweeney_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Sweeney_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Kate Sweeney (2014). <i>American Afterlife: Encounters in the Customs of Mourning</i>. University of George Press. pp.&#160;4\u20135. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8203-4600-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-8203-4600-7\">978-0-8203-4600-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Afterlife%3A+Encounters+in+the+Customs+of+Mourning&amp;rft.pages=4-5&amp;rft.pub=University+of+George+Press&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8203-4600-7&amp;rft.au=Kate+Sweeney&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACooling+board\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lyricsbox.com/donny-hathaway-lyrics-thank-you-master-for-my-soul-dmwlvqr.html\">\"Thank You, Master (For My Soul)\"</a> at Lyricsbox</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Marling (2008) <i>Ice: Great Moments in the History of Hard, Cold Water</i> <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-87351-628-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-87351-628-0\">978-0-87351-628-0</a>. Minnesota Historical Society, p. 62.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gray188_no_text_bw.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Gray188_no_text_bw.png/30px-Gray188_no_text_bw.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"28\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Gray188_no_text_bw.png/45px-Gray188_no_text_bw.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Gray188_no_text_bw.png/60px-Gray188_no_text_bw.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"500\" data-file-height=\"463\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Death\" title=\"Death\">death</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Cooling_board&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Death-stub\" title=\"Template:Death-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Death-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Death-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><l